cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and language detection on Twitter.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a possible category as the paper mentions using recurrent neural networks to automatically learn meaningful representations of mixed-language data.
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses training machine learning models with raw features and word embeddings.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve language detection accuracy.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but it is mentioned in the paper that code-switching is a socially motivated phenomenon, which could fall under this category.
